creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 130 by Various.
Read in English by Kasper; David Wales; Bellona Times; Winston Tharp; Craig Campbell; JennTH; Son of the Exiles; Little Tee; Andrea Coffee; Michael Armenta; Jeanie

This is a collection of 17 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for March 2014. Selections this month are as follows:

Adam's Curse by William Butler Yeats
Ballade of the Book-Hunter by Andrew Lang
The Bee by Sidney Lanier
By The Sea by Emily Dickinson
Charles the Twelfth of Sweden Rides in the Ukraine by Rainer Maria Rilke
The Child of Mercy by Johann Gottfried Herder
The Dying Indian by Philip Freneau
The Glorious Twelfth at Jindabye by Victor Daley
God Made This Day For Me by Edgar A. Guest
The Little Hand by Frances Sargent Osgood
Love Song by Rainer Maria Rilke
People at Night by Rainer Maria Rilke
The Phoenix and the Turtle by William Shakespeare
The Poets of the Tomb by Henry Lawson
Time, Real and Imaginary: An Allegory by Samuel Taylor Coleridge
The Women of the West by George Essex Evans
The Yellow Violet by William Cullen Bryant

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

M4B Format Available
